UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2093
1 AN ACT relating to limited commercial driver's licenses and declaring an
2 emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 281A IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 In accordance with 49 C.F.R. sec. 383.3 exemptions for certain restricted CDLs, the
7 cabinet shall promulgate emergency and ordinary administrative regulations in
8 accordance with KRS Chapter 13A to extend the allowable time length of a limited
9 CDL to the maximum length allowed under the federal regulation accordance with 49
10 C.F.R sec. 383.3.
11 Section 2. Whereas on September 29, 2022, 49 C.F.R sec. 383.3(f)(3)(ii) was
12 amended to allow states that issue limited commercial driver's licenses to increase the
13 allowable usage within a 12-month period from 180 days to 210 days, and the
14 Transportation Cabinet has not taken action to comply with this federal regulation, an
15 emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by
16 the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
